      "span_text": "In exactly the same way we can define D X for any n-element subset X of N × N. Bergeron, Garsia, and Tesler [CITATION_1] then conjecture (and prove in some special cases) for several classes of subsets X that dim C (∂D X ) = k X n! for some positive integer k X ; and in fact ∂D X , regarded as an S n -module, affords k X copies of the regular representation.",
